==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|nusaunce|lang=fro}}, {{term|nussance}} etc., from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|nuisance|lang=fro}}, from {{term|nuisir||to harm}} (, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|noceō||I harm}}, {{m|la|nocēre}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-nuisance.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈnuːsəns/}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈnjuːsəns/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A [[minor]] [[annoyance]] or [[inconvenience]].
# A person or thing causing annoyance or inconvenience.
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} Anything [[harmful]] or [[offensive]] to the community or to a member of it, for which a legal remedy exists.
#: ''a public '''nuisance'''''

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|minor annoyance or inconvenience}} [[annoyance]], [[inconvenience]], [[offense]]
* {{sense|person or thing causing annoyance or inconvenience}} [[bother]], [[obstacle]], [[pest]]

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|minor annoyance or inconvenience}} [[enjoyment]]

